Package org.anchoranalysis.image.voxel.iterator

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IntBinaryOperation
    A binary operation on two int-values that produces an int
    ProcessVoxel
    Processes a 3D point
    ProcessVoxelSlice<T extends Buffer>
    Processes a 3D point like ProcessVoxel but also retrieves a VoxelBuffer for the current z-slice.
    ProcessVoxelSliceBuffer<T extends Buffer>
    Processes a 3D point like ProcessVoxel but also retrieves a Buffer for the current z-slice.
    ProcessVoxelSliceTwo<S extends Buffer,​T extends Buffer>
    Processes a 3D point like ProcessVoxel but also retrieves two VoxelBuffers for the current z-slice.
    ProcessVoxelThreeSliceBuffers<T extends Buffer>
    Processes a 3D point like ProcessVoxel but also retrieves three Buffer for the current z-slice.
    ProcessVoxelTwoSliceBuffers<T extends Buffer>
    Processes a 3D point like ProcessVoxel but also retrieves two Buffer for the current z-slice.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    IterateVoxels
    Iterate over voxels in an extent/bounding-box/mask calling a processor on each selected voxel
    IterateVoxelsByte  
    IterateVoxelsVoxelBoxAsInt
    Iterates over Voxels using the (slower) getInt and putInt methods of VoxelBuffer rather than directly accessing the buffers
    RetrieveBufferForSlice<T extends Buffer>
    Exposes a ProcessVoxel as a ProcessVoxelSliceBuffer by retrieving a buffer from voxels for each z-slice.
    RetrieveBuffersForThreeSlices<T extends Buffer>
    Exposes a ProcessVoxel as a ProcessVoxelSliceBuffer by retrieving three buffers for each z-slice.
    RetrieveBuffersForTwoSlices<T extends Buffer>
    Exposes a ProcessVoxel as a ProcessVoxelSliceBuffer by retrieving two buffers from voxels for each z-slice.
